data.description: Immediate equity. Priced $40k below market value. Lots of upgrades including over range microwave, insulated garage doors with openers, exterior lights all LED dusk to dawn, interior lights all LED, smart thermostat, and wall mounted smart TV over fireplace. Recently graded back driveway to garage and back patio. Two new freeze proof water spigots, one in the garage and at the back patio. Spacious 3097 sf home on 2.07 acre lot with a huge side lot and a small creek at the back of the property. Cedar shingle exterior windows caulked and painted 2020 with covered front porch.  Near restaurants and grocery with a country feel. Easy commute to Charlotte and Monroe area.  Enter into an updated entry with hardwood flooring, living space with trey ceiling , a lovely wide stairway takes you down to a half bath adjoining the 2 car garage. Large open kitchen, dining, and living area with fireplace just off the entry area. A freshly painted hallway leads to 3 bedrooms, bath and master bedroom with adjoining second bath. Right off the kitchen is a laundry area, half bath, large bonus room, closets, office and storage area. Schedule a viewing to see if this might be the perfect home for you and your family.  Home is being sold as is.
data.whatILove: The country feel with a stream in the back while still in town and only an hour commute to Charlotte. Fiber optic internet service with average utility bill below $100. Side lot big enough for another house or pool or poll barn.
